gomodel:SYNGO_381  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Wang et al performed biotinylation experiments in order to verify plasma membrane expression of ClC-3. Shortly, the authors use membrane impermeable NHS-biotin derivate in order to biotinylate plasma membrane proteins exposed to the extracellular surface of cultured rat hippocampal neurons (Fig. 5A). Furthermore, ClC-3 expression on the synaptic plasma membrane surface was examined by preparation of synaptic vesicle and membrane fractions from rat hippocampi followed by immunodetection of ClC-3 and plasma membrane and SV marker proteins (Fig. 5B). In addition, in a double immunogold labeling EM experiment on isolated plasma membrane fraction, PSD95 and ClC-3 surface expression was confirmed. In order to validate the postsynaptic expression of ClC-3, as determined biochemically and by EM, Wang et al perfomed immunofluorescene experiments on cultured rat hippocampal neurons and showed colocalization of the chloride channel with PSD95 and NMDAR (Fig. 6 A and B). Association of ClC-3 with postsynaptic membranes was confirmed biochemically by immunoprecipitation of PSD95 and ClC-3 and Western blot detection of postsynaptic and plasma membrane proteins (Fig. 6C).\n\n6/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Neuronal Cultures\nWe have previously used hippocampal neurons cultured from E17-\nP30 animals as a model of postnatal development (Marks et al.,\n2005; Marks et al., 2000). Briefly, isoflurane-anesthetized rats or\nmice were decapitated, the hippocampi removed, sectioned\n(400 mM), and incubated in oxygenated, pH-buffered saline.\n\nSurface Biotinylation\nBiotinylation of plasma membrane proteins having an extracellular\ndomain was performed on cultures of hippocampal neurons from\nE18 Sprague-Dawley rats, using a water-soluble, membrane imper-\nmeant, and thiol-cleavable biotin reagent, as described previously\n(Davis et al., 1998) with minor modifications.\n\nIsolation of Synaptosomal Membranes\nSynaptosomal membranes and synaptic vesicles were isolated as\ndescribed elsewhere (Huttner et al., 1983; Thoidis et al., 1998; Wat-\nson et al., 1994) with minor modifications. All centrifugations were\ncarried out at 4°C. Hippocampi freshly isolated from adult rats\nwere homogenized in an ice-cold buffer containing sucrose\n(0.3 M), HEPES (10 mM), and protease inhibitor cocktail (1:500,\nSigma) (pH 7.3)." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_381" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

